    <item>
      <title>Open BSD and Zen</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/essays/openbsdzen/index.html</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Jun 2025 12:48:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/essays/openbsdzen/index.html</guid>
      <description>OpenBSD and Zen I’ve been using OpenBSD for a long time.&#xA;I’ve been sitting Zen for about two years, in the tradition of Seungsahn, with Ryōkan as a guide.&#xA;Nobody asked me to connect these two things. But they kept connecting themselves.&#xA;This is me trying to say why.&#xA;Less is not a compromise OpenBSD ships without a lot of things other systems include by default.&#xA;That’s a choice. Every piece of code that isn’t there is a piece of code that can’t have a vulnerability.</description>
